    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1951-10-12T14:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1951-10-12T14:00:00-05:00" n="322"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d322">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.5/10–1251: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Turkey</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_WG1"
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Wadsworth</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                    <note n="1" xml:id="d322fn1">Repeated to London, Cairo, and Paris for <persName
                            corresp="#p_MDI1">MacArthur</persName>.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">top secret</hi>
                        <lb/>
                        <gloss target="#t_niact1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">niact</hi>
                        </gloss>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Ankara</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1951-10-12T21:00:00+02:00"
                            >October 12, 1951—9 p. m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>349. Tripartite mil mission arrived Ankara at noon and in course formal calls on
                    Min <gloss target="#t_NATO1">NAT</gloss> Def, <gloss target="#t_FonMin1"
                        >FonMin</gloss>, Chief Gen Staff and <gloss target="#t_PriMin1"
                        >PriMin</gloss>, has reed sincere welcome and assurances Turkey’s keen
                    desire make maximum contribution to <gloss target="#t_NATO1">NATO</gloss> and
                        <gloss target="#t_ME1">ME</gloss> defense. Mtg with <gloss
                        target="#t_PriMin1">PriMin</gloss> continued half-hour beyond allotted
                    time.</p>
                <p>Three points made by him merit special mention: <list>
                        <label>1.</label>
                        <item>
                            <gloss target="#t_PriMin1">PriMin</gloss> himself would preside
                            tomorrow’s all-day “business” session. He would be assisted by Min
                                <gloss target="#t_NATO1">NAT</gloss> Def, <gloss target="#t_FonMin1"
                                >FonMin</gloss> and Chief Gen Staff and their principal assistants.
                            He asked and we agreed that three mil chiefs be accompanied by their
                            chief assistants and by Brit, French and US Ambassadors.</item>
                        <label>2.</label>
                        <item>He fully shared our view that, if Egyptian Govt extended invitation,
                            tripartite mil mission shld become quadripartite,<note n="2"
                                xml:id="d322fn2">See editorial note, <hi rend="italic">infra.</hi>
                            </note> a Turk general with appropriate assistants to accompany them on
                            Cairo visit. <gloss target="#t_PriMin1">PriMin</gloss> and <gloss
                                target="#t_FonMin1">FonMin</gloss> felt strongly such visit highly
                            desirable this time on political as well as mil grounds, always assuming
                            receipt of formal invitation from Egyptian Govt.</item>
                        <label>3.</label>
                        <item>Towards end meeting <gloss target="#t_PriMin1">PriMin</gloss> handed
                            each mil chief a copy of top secret memo entitled “The Position of
                            Turkey in the North Atlantic Treaty Org”. Full text is given in my
                            immediately fol tel.<note n="3" xml:id="d322fn3">Telegram 350 from
                                Ankara of October 13, not printed, reported the Turkish estimate of
                                Turkey’s strategic position, its present armed strength, its
                                potential wartime strength, and its military, economic, and
                                financial needs (740.5/10-1351).</note> We shall study it this
                            evening, discuss it with Turks tomorrow and report reactions
                                thereafter.<note n="4" xml:id="d322fn4">For documentation on the
                                Conference of U.S., U.K., and French Representatives with Turkish
                                Prime Minister and Staff at Ankara on 13 and 14 October 1951, see
                                    <ref target="frus1951v05">volume <hi rend="smallcaps">v</hi>
                                </ref>.</note>
                        </item>
                    </list>
                </p>
                <p>Gen <persName corresp="#p_BON1">Bradley</persName> concurs.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_WG1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Wadsworth</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
